# Strava API Configuration
# To enable live Strava data fetching, you'll need to:
# 1. Create a Strava API application at https://www.strava.com/settings/api
# 2. Get your Client ID and Client Secret
# 3. Complete the OAuth flow to get a refresh token
# 4. Add these values to your .env.local file

# Your Strava application's Client ID
STRAVA_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here

# Your Strava application's Client Secret  
STRAVA_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# Your refresh token (obtained through OAuth flow)
STRAVA_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token_here

# Instructions for getting a refresh token:
# 1. Go to: https://www.strava.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID&response_type=code&redirect_uri=http://localhost&approval_prompt=force&scope=read,activity:read_all
# 2. Replace YOUR_CLIENT_ID with your actual client ID
# 3. Authorize the application and copy the 'code' parameter from the redirect URL
# 4. Make a POST request to exchange the code for tokens:
#    curl -X POST https://www.strava.com/oauth/token \
#      -F client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID \
#      -F client_secret=YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET \
#      -F code=YOUR_AUTHORIZATION_CODE \
#      -F grant_type=authorization_code
# 5. Use the refresh_token from the response